job_description:
Who we are:
Established in Melbourne in 2015, Airwallex is a global payments fintech transforming the way businesses move and manage money domestically and internationally. We have built a global financial infrastructure platform to help businesses transact, collect and pay across 130+ countries and 50+ currencies, without the constraints of the traditional global financial system.
Airwallex is Australia's fastest growing fintech unicorn. We've grown to 13 global locations and have raised over $500 million in funding. Airwallex has been recognised in Forbes Cloud 100 2020, and placed in the Top 50 of KPMG's Global Fintech100 two years in a row. To support our ambitious growth plans, we're looking for smart, collaborative and passionate people who are looking to make a genuine impact.
The role:
This role will work closely with the Engineering, UX and business functions across the Airwallex environment, focusing on strategic development and management of client-facing product.
Responsibilities:
1. Lead product development from ideation through to final delivery and commercialisation
2. Build out our product management function, mentoring our current cohort or PMs and recruiting new ones
3. Partner with Internal and External Stakeholders to identify and deliver product solutions that increase both revenue and commercialisation rates, and decrease client enquiries
4. Collaborate with Senior Management, Software Engineering and the broader Product team during the analysis phase to assess value, usability and feasibility;
5. Define KPIs to measure success of product along with post-delivery reporting to track product performance for multiple internal stakeholders;
6. Own the prioritized backlog of work with the development team and manage prioritization decisions along with Management and Development team members to align delivery with the Product roadmap;
7. Make difficult trade-offs and decisions relating to product features, cost, and schedule.
Qualifications:
1. Previous experience in product management;
2. Able to make decisions by considering both long term product vison and short term growth requirement;
3. Exceptional communication skills, primarily focusing on translating between technical and non-technical audiences;
4. Detail oriented and ability to stay focused on what is important to users and the business
5. Capable of leading a team and getting people excited about your product vision.
6. Ability to identify gaps and the flexibility to manage and close them with relevant team members.
